TITLE: Defining Collections with Schemas (Velite)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet illustrates how to define content collections with their associated schemas in Velite. It uses `defineCollection` to configure each collection (authors, posts, tags), and exports the configuration using `defineConfig`. The schemas define the structure and validation rules for the content items in each collection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zce/velite/blob/main/docs/guide/define-collections.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { defineCollection, defineConfig, s } from 'velite'

const posts = defineCollection({
  /* collection shema options */
})

const authors = defineCollection({
  /* collection shema options */
})

const tags = defineCollection({
  /* collection shema options */
})

export default defineConfig({
  collections: { authors, posts, tags }
})
```

