TITLE: Using s.metadata() to Parse Document Metadata (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: The `s.metadata()` schema parses markdown content and returns metadata such as reading time and word count. It extracts information from the document body.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zce/velite/blob/main/docs/guide/velite-schemas.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
metadata: s.metadata()
// document body => { readingTime: 2, wordCount: 100 }
```

