TITLE: Define a Validation Schema in Velite (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a validation schema using Velite's `defineSchema` and `s` (extended Zod) for validating a title, email, and a custom validation for checking if a string is equal to 'hello'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zce/velite/blob/main/docs/guide/custom-schema.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { defineSchema, s } from 'velite'

// `s` is extended from Zod with some custom schemas,
// `s` also includes all members of zod, so you can use `s` as `z`

// for validating title
export const title = defineSchema(() => s.string().min(1).max(100))

// for validating email
export const email = defineSchema(() => s.string().email({ message: 'Invalid email address' }))

// custom validation logic
export const hello = defineSchema(() =>
  s.string().refine(value => {
    if (value !== 'hello') {
      return 'Value must be "hello"'
    }
    return true
  })
)
```

