TITLE: Typed Routes example with Velite and Next.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use the `typedRoutes` experimental feature of Velite to get typed routes in a Next.js application.  It defines a schema for a content collection using Velite and then uses the defined route type to provide type safety for links created with `next/link`.  It includes TypeScript types for the `Route` and `Schema` objects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zce/velite/blob/main/docs/guide/with-nextjs.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import type { Route } from 'next'
import type { Schema } from 'velite'

const options = defineCollection({
  // ...
  schema: s.object({
    // ...
    link: z.string() as Schema<Route<'/posts/${string}'>>
  })
})
```

