TITLE: Define Collection with Schema
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to define a collection with a schema using the `defineCollection` function. The schema is defined using `s.object` and specifies the data structure of the collection items, extracting data from frontmatter and markdown body.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zce/velite/blob/main/docs/reference/config.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const posts = defineCollection({
  schema: s.object({
    title: s.string(), // from frontmatter
    description: s.string().optional(), // from frontmatter
    excerpt: s.string(), // from markdown body,
    content: s.string() // from markdown body
  })
})
```

