TITLE: Using s.markdown() to Parse Markdown Content (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: The `s.markdown(options)` schema parses markdown content and returns the corresponding HTML.  It uses the configured markdown processing options.  Options include `gfm`, `removeComments`, and `copyLinkedFiles`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zce/velite/blob/main/docs/guide/velite-schemas.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
content: s.markdown()
// => html content
```

