TITLE: Directory Structure Example
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates the recommended directory structure for organizing content collections within a Velite project. Each top-level directory represents a separate collection, containing content files like YAML and Markdown files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zce/velite/blob/main/docs/guide/define-collections.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Diff
CODE:
```
content
├── authors # => authors collection
│   ├── zce.yml
│   └── jane.yml
├── posts # => posts collection
│   ├── hello-world.md
│   └── another-post.md
└── tags # => tags collection
    └── all-in-one.yml
