TITLE: Using s.slug() to Validate Unique Slug Values (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: The `s.slug(by, reserved)` schema validates a slug, ensuring it is unique within a collection (`by`), not a reserved value, and conforms to a slug format. It combines uniqueness checks with format validation. It can return 'Slug already exists', 'Slug is reserved', or 'Invalid slug' issues.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zce/velite/blob/main/docs/guide/velite-schemas.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
slug: s.slug('taxonomies', ['admin', 'login'])
// case 1. unique slug value
// 'hello-world' => 'hello-world'

// case 2. non-unique value (in all unique by 'taxonomies')
// 'hello-world' => issue 'Slug already exists'

// case 3. reserved slug value
// 'admin' => issue 'Slug is reserved'

// case 4. invalid slug value
// 'Hello World' => issue 'Invalid slug'
```

