TITLE: Content Body Access (Velite)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to access the raw content body and plain text body directly from `meta.content` and `meta.plain` using a custom schema and the `.transform()` method. This allows you to incorporate the content directly into the collection's schema.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zce/velite/blob/main/docs/guide/define-collections.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const posts = defineCollection({
  schema: s.object({
    content: s.custom().transform((data, { meta }) => meta.content),
    plain: s.custom().transform((data, { meta }) => meta.plain)
  })
})
```

